{
  "Internal Rate of Return (IRR)": "内部返回率(IRR)",
  "This lesson covers the fundamental measures of center used to analyze and summarize data sets. You'll learn how to calculate and apply the mean, median, and mode, and understand when each is most appropriate.": "这个课程涵盖了分析和总结数据集的中心的基本测量方法。 您将学会如何计算和应用平均值、 中位数和模式, 并了解何时最合适 。",
  "What is the Internal Rate of Return (IRR)?": "国内返回率(IRR)是多少?",
  "IRR is the annualized rate of return that sets NPV to zero. It represents the project's true percentage return, accounting for the time value of money and the pattern of cash flows.": "IRR是将NPV设为零的年化回报率。它代表了项目的真实百分比回报率,反映了资金的时间价值和现金流量模式。",
  "What is a hurdle rate?": "什么是障碍率?",
  "The hurdle rate is the minimum acceptable rate of return for an investment. Projects with IRR above the hurdle rate are accepted; those below are rejected. It typically equals or exceeds the company's cost of capital.": "障碍率是投资最低可接受的收益率。 超过障碍率的IRR项目被接受;以下的项目被否决,通常等于或超过公司的资本成本。",
  "What is the payback period?": "偿还期是多少?",
  "The payback period measures how long it takes to recoup the initial investment from cash inflows. It is simple to calculate but ignores the time value of money and cash flows beyond the payback date.": "回报期衡量初始投资从现金流入中回收需要多长时间。 计算很简单,但忽略了偿还日之后货币和现金流量的时间价值。",
  "What is the discounted payback period?": "贴现偿还期是多少?",
  "The discounted payback period improves upon the simple payback by discounting each cash flow before accumulating them. It tells you how long until you recover your investment in present-value terms.": "贴现回扣期通过在积累之前对每个现金流进行贴现,在简单回扣后会有所改进。 它告诉您要多久才能收回按现值计算的投资。",
  "What is the 'scale problem' with IRR?": "IRR的“规模问题”是什么?",
  "Since IRR is a percentage, it does not reflect the dollar amount of value created. A 30% return on $1,000 ($300) creates far less wealth than a 15% return on $1,000,000 ($150,000).": "由于IRR是一个百分比,它并不反映所创造的价值的美元数额。 以1 000美元(300美元)计的收益率30%远低于以1 000 000美元(150 000美元)计的15%的收益率财富。",
  "A venture capitalist invests $1 million in a startup that returns $5 million after 5 years. What is the annualized IRR?": "风险资本家投资100万美元启动,五年后回报500万美元。 年度IRR是什么?",
  "IRR = (Exit Value / Entry Price)^(1/years) - 1 = ($5M / $1M)^(1/5) - 1 = 5^0.2 - 1 = 1.3797 - 1 = 0.3797, approximately 38%. This is the annualized return over the 5-year holding period.": "IRR = (出口价值/进入价格) = (1年) - 1 = (5M / $1M) = (1/5) - 1 = 5.0.2 - 1 = 1. 3797 - 1 = 0.37977, 约38%,这是5年持有期的年回报率。",
  "Another VC invests $1 million for a $10 million exit in 7 years. What is the approximate IRR?": "另一个VC投资100万美元 7年内出口1000万美元",
  "IRR = (10/1)^(1/7) - 1 = 10^(0.1429) - 1 = 1.3895 - 1 = 0.3895, approximately 39%. Despite a 10x return vs. 5x, the IRR is similar because it took 7 years instead of 5.": "IRR = (10/1)(1/7-1) - 1 = 10(0.1429) - 1 = 1.3895 - 1 = 0.3895 - 1 = 0.3895, = 0.3895, 约为 39%。尽管回报为10x 相对于 5x, IRR 却相似,因为它用了7年而不是5年。",
  "Multiple IRRs can occur when:": "在下列情况下,可发生多种IRR:",
  "When cash flows alternate between positive and negative more than once (non-conventional cash flows), the NPV equation can have multiple solutions, producing multiple IRRs and making the metric unreliable.": "当现金流量在一次以上(非常规现金流量)正向和负向之间交替流动时,非常规现金流量等式可以有多种解决办法,产生多种IRR,并使衡量标准不可靠。"
}